caption: My favorite Italian restaurant in St Louis. I can't wait for them to reopen.
Family went here for 30 years over Christmas holidays. Best salads ever. Request extra artichokes!
italian food and the setting here is excellent. I had a brother come into town and he asked me to go back here. The bill was decent.
Outstanding spot for italian food. Arrived at seven, it wasn't crowded. I can see why they have a lot of great reviews.
Alfredo was very uncooked and so were my parents food. It was my first time here and this was not a good first impression.
Their pasta is amazing!! Without a doubt some of the best pasta I've had in my life. Their cocktails are fantastic to match. Definitely recommend this place.
italian food... so delicious. i will be back with my friends. bring your appetite because portions are filling.

Not authentic Italian. And the waitress was terrible - didn’t accurately describe dishes, asked us about dessert and gave us bill before I finished my entree, was unable to explain what wines were available by the glass.. Had to send linguine with clam sauce back - who makes linguine with clams in a cream sauce???  The spaghetti Bolognese was just spaghetti with marinara sauce and a meatball on top. Prices are high for the quality. Would not return.
It Was Our "Date Night" And I Had Nothing But A Great Time! Timothy Was The Best. The Food Was Amazing. Defiantly Going Back
Love the friendly folks at this restaurant. Always go above and beyond to make my dining experience the best ever.

We were in town for a wedding during COVID-19, so we were very thrilled with the precautions being taken by the restaurant and staff to maintain social distancing. We enjoyed pre dinner cocktails and everyone was happy with their meal. Felt like an authentic Italian restaurant. Priced well, an easy walk from the Hyatt where we stayed and overall an enjoyable dining experience!
Great place to take wife and kids.
Great lasagna, nice atmosphere, very friendly.
Love this place and will miss seeing Mr. Gitto.

If you love the Cardinals (or sports period) and Italian food, or even just one of the two, this is a do not miss in STL. Pasta is the best around, but the atmosphere and sports memorabilia. This is an STL institution. I'll miss seeing Charlie Sr. (RIP) in the restaurant and at the bar.

This is my favorite place in the city to grab a drink. Bartending here is a work of art. The very best dirty martinis by far and if you are a bourbon drinker (or not but want to be) just ask Louie or India to make one for you. Unbelievable, I didn't even like bourbon before I started coming here. Place is amazing, 3 generations here almost every night. This is the original Charlie Gittos and in my opinion the best because of the history.  7/10/20 update.  The thought of Charlie Gitto never being at the corner of the bar with his heater running brings a tears to my eyes. What a great guy and touched so many. Great owners set their businesses up for success just as he did. As I sit here tonight eating one of the best dishes of tortellini I have ever eaten here, I know that the tradition of this restaurant will continue and grow.  Louie Vangel has done an amazing job of training the new cooks and this is my second meal this month that has blown me away with the improvements. Top it off with an India Farrance cocktail 🍸 and you just can’t get a better combination. For those of you that know me get it, I do come here all the time, but I’m telling you, the food has never been better in the last four years than it has my last two visits. But that’s what great owners do. You will be missed Charlie and never forgotten.
As always, great service, great food and the best privately owned restaurant in downtown St. Louis.  Can't go wrong even with a limited menu.
1 star even a lot this place services was very slow. They didnt had full menu. I would never come back here. Food is very expensive. If u wanna go to restaurant  go to mexican restaurants
Good food and service.
Excellent food.  Hard to judge the service because we had a large group.
Nice little old school Italian eatery. Love the photos and the local ties.
The pasta was dried out!  They did nothing to try a resolve the issue.  It is a shame,this use to be a great place!  Not any more.  Disgusting!
The Italian sandwich I had was incredible. Attentive service, fun place to visit.
Enjoyed the toasted ravioli.

Wonderful pasta house with good service. They have an outstanding red sauce, which is key to many Italian dishes. Started with French onion soup, which was very good. Cheese was possibly white cheddar maybe. But regardless the French onion was worthy of ordering again.  Wonderful spaghetti with meat sauce. Highly recommend this place!  Service was good as well. Doesn’t look like much from the outside but the ambience inside is nice.

Had dinner last week at Charlie Gitto's Downtown for the first time and it was fantastic! Excellent food, service & an inviting family atmosphere. Very friendly staff and management. Can't wait to return!

Really was disappointed.  The service was not bad but the food was terrible. I was really looking forward to some good old Italian food and was left with cold and not good tasting noodles and sauce. I would choose Many other places besides this place.
Very good 👍👌👌
Let's be honest, you're mainly interested in the toasted ravioli. Same with us, I'm happy to say it was amazing and worth the trip here!
Great food and atmosphere. Nice little neighborhood eatery

Friendly. Fast. Tasty. We were downtown for a convention and were running out of time to grab dinner before the evening session started. We popped in here and it was incredible. We explained we were in a bit of a rush and the staff were so accommodating.  The carbonara was really tasty but the cheesy bread was AMAZING.
We love this place, they always seem to have a table for us, the food is always delicious.
Toasted ravioli and lasagna are delicious.
A laid back authentic Italian restaurant that is a must if you're downtown! This place is a St. Louis classic!
Great Italian Food with decent Vegetarian options
The only place that can take the place of Gittos downtown is Gittos on the hill , outstanding food and service
Great old school Italian eatery with Italian classics.

My daughter and I stopped in for dinner while visiting St. Louis.  Looking to try toasted ravioli since it is locally famous.  They were alright, but nothing special. Only come with meat stuffing. Ordered spaghetti bolognese and salad for main course. The spaghetti was drowning in sauce. Sauce was kind of sweet for my taste.  Salad was drenched in italian dressing.  All in all it was ok, but not likely to go back.
The toasted ravioli and the butter cake were great but the pizza was truly awful. I have never tasted worse cheese on a pizza before. The sauce for the roasted ravioli could be a little less watery.
Nice place... Good food!!!

Visiting from out of the state so we wanted to try some fried ravioli and one of us had to eat gluten free also. They had gf pasta and several things on the menu to choose from. The fried ravioli was yummy. Loved the laid- back atmosphere, attentive service and reasonable prices. Food was really good. Try it! You won't be disappointed.
Great cocktails and even better service!
Amazing Italian! Love the toasted ravioli! Canaloni was super!
I sampled their pizza and it was a breadless, overly cheesey mess with no additional flavor. They earned a star back with decent pasta but I doubt I'll be giving them a second attempt.
(Translated by Google) It is not entirely clean  (Original) No es del todo limpio
Favorite

Upon arrival there we were told it would be a 30 min wait. No big deal but the restaurant started to empty right away. We waited until 30 min passed and then we were seated at one of the 12+ tables that we saw open. Annoying but okay, we heard the food was good so we were optimistic. Ordered ravioli app not great but edible. Our entrees completely lacked any flavor at all, way over cooked chicken and bland pasta sauces. Server was nice but never refilled our drinks or asked if we wanted another beer. I would never recommend this place to anyone, it really was one of the worst Italian restaurants I have ever been to. Super bummed we went here, if you visit St. Louis find a different Italian restaurant!
Food tastes good, server needs training.

I miss the Chesterfield location and think the employees and manager from there should all come to downtown and help them. The menu was not the same as well. My food was fantastic, I ate the lasagna  and the waitress was nice. I love the local feel and pictures. Definitely casual and affordable and fun to hang with friends.
There's so much history on and in these walls!! A STL tradition!
Awesome food and the best waitresses!!
THE Italian restaurant in St. Louis. The best lasagna you've ever had is here.
Very good food, had spaghetti bolognese. The tables are very close, really too close to be comfortable, otherwise a 5 star.
Worst Italian ever. Save your self some time and go to the Hill.
Outstanding food and service!!
The food was very good
A friend recommended this restaurant and we absolutely loved it. Great place to watch the Cardinals game and the food was fabulous. We are definitely going back for more the next time we are in town.
This place is filled with so much sports history!!! And the toasted ravioli is pretty good too! The staff (Katrina) was very prompt, kind, and attentive! Good food, good ambiance, and great service!

First time in St. Louis and had dinner at this establishment. I waited what seemed like forever to get my food (considering we had a large party). However, it was worth the wait. I ordered the seafood ravioli and I was extremely pleased.
Quaint little hole in the wall.. honestly if we had not checked it out on Google probably would have skirted by it!
After the third hair i pulled out of my small salad, I got a little grossed out. But my sandwich was decent.

I always liked this place until the last time I visited. The waiter was too busy watching the game. So it was slow service and the food was lukewarm. It's a shame because it was always one of my favorite restaurants.

I usually don't leave bad reviews but i felt like i needed to. Their service was aweful and the waitress was very rude. It took her 20 minutes to get us water even before we ordered, plus they were not busy.
Excellent wait staff, very friendly, food was delicious
Best buffalo pizza ever!
Always enjoy eating here.
Great friendly service and incredible food
it's  a classic. great lunch specials daily,
Delicious, laid back, right in the heart of downtown. Try the house salad, seafood risotto, and shrimp scampi.
Great Italian food in a historic setting.

Oh yea! Red sauce (was taught by some friends of northern extraction and Italian heritage that it is correctly referred to as 'gravy'? ..... That dog don't hunt down south... I digress) is among the best had anywhere ever. Good service. Atmosphere is a slice of life. History on the walls. The souls that have passed through the doors have all contributed to a one of a kind place.
Great food & awesome service.

I loved it! Old St Louis staple and this was my first visit. Had the chicken parmigiana lunch special and it was great. They have an excellent house salad too. Service was fast and friendly. Only minor complaint is they only had pink packets for tea and basically no ice in the iced tea. Those are really minor though. Food and service wa great!
Good Italian food and a great atmosphere
The food was great and the atmosphere was very relaxing. The chicken parm is so delicious and filling.
The Charlie Gitto's house is the best salad in town!

This place is EXCELLENT! The staff, the ambiance and food are all out of this world. Walking distance from the baseball stadium. Prices are very reasonable and the portions are large. The place itself is full of memorabilia and pictures of local celebrities and athletes from all sports teams. Truly a very enjoyable experience. Will certainly return
The BEST lasagna ever!

Looking for Italian while in St. Louis, close to hotel, Googled and found Charlie Grittos, glad I did.  Excellent little Italian Restaurant.  Great Atmosphere with all the photos on the wall.  Great Staff very attentive.  Great Food, I had the House Salad and Veal Parm it was great.  The olive oil on the Spaghetti added a very nice touch.
Best Italian I have ever had!

The staff was wonderful. Although they were working they still had smiles on their faces and looked happy to help. We got lucky being sat because we had a party of 8 without a reservation so if you want to eat here call first! Anyway, everyone in our group seemed to like their food except me. I got the Caesar salad and the toasted ravioli appetizer. The salad was good but the raviolis were gross. They were toasted perfectly but the meat inside reminded me of cat food in a can. It was a weird texture and a weird taste so I wouldn’t recommend ordering them. They carry a vanilla flavored light beer called love gun from a local brewery and it’s pretty tasty. The restaurant was clean and the decor was aged but it worked. The waitstaff was great and the cooks were fast. I had a nice time and so did my group.
Nice little Italian Spot. Fit for foodies or a stop before the game.
I'm not from the area, so I don't know how this place compares to other places in St Louis, but it wasn't that good. The Caesar salad had too much dressing. The sauce on the chicken parm was bland.

Stop in for a quick bite to eat before the game and had an outstanding meal. We couldn't have been more pleased with the quality the food or the service. If you're going to Saint Louis to watch a ball game make sure you stop by this place.
Cool

This is painful for me to write as I love Charlie Gittos on the Hill, but this place made me some of the worst food I've ever had at a restaurant. Pasta was overpriced and bland.  Please take your friends and loves ones to the Charlie Gittos on the hill, which is a 5 star restaurant
Great salads. Quick service.
Great Italian Food. A St. Louis icon.
We came here on a recommendation from a friend. Madison took fantastic care of us. The food was top notch. We will definitely be coming back here the  next time we are in St. Louis!
Fabulous entrees!
A Downtown StL institution.
Great food, Great service, Great atmosphere. The place to eat in downtown St. Louis
Had the cod. It was overcooked and rubbery. Perhaps to be expected at an Italian place. The pasta should be better
Best lasagna ever!

For what I paid for my food (baked lasagna) I would expect more than 3 noodles. Very disappointing. If you have a very small appetite and have alot of money to waste this place is for you. If your hungry and want a decent meal dont waste your time. Rip off for sure.
Wasnt very good at all. The service was good that was about it. Very pricey and small portions.
The home of toasted ravioli
Excellent food and service. The atmosphere is neat with lots of memorabilia.  Salad is very good and pasta dishes are very filling. The toasted ravioli taste homemade!
Great food and service is quick. All the photos on the wall are nice
Best Italian food I've had.
Food was ok.
Good food, good service
Great history
Very good food 👍
Fabulous food and great vibe!
Always delicious!  I've been coming to Charlie Gitto's for more then 30 years, the food is always delicious. Love this place. Tons of St Louis History.

Haven’t been back to St. Louis in years, but have dreamed about the last meal I had at Gitto’s. Unfortunately, my favorite item was off the menu and the next best meal lacked quality for a $25 dollar seafood pasta meal.  So lacking I had to get another meal after and I don’t go for seconds or desert normally.  Food comes out fast as if they are pushing tables.  Not the atmosphere that I remember and recommended friends to.  Last visit, sorry Charlie.
The place is very cool with lots of memorabilia that had been collected thru the years, the service was nice and attentive but the food was just so so.
Food was good, but our waitress was terrible!
Awesome as usual
The salad let me down.
The food was very good. I loved the chicken parm. The service was pretty good. The only complaint and that is one of our glasses was pretty dirty

You always have to check your food when you get orders to go and they do not want to be responsible for anything even when they are completely wrong.  Wasting water on customers, getting orders wrong and it's always well you should have done this...just simply take responsibly and correct the problem!
Walked out full and happy

Good service, decent food and lively atmosphere. Not a fan of the toasted ravioli, gnocchi was good, it would have been better in a cream sauce. The chicken in the chicken risotto was burned, however the risotto was cooked well.
Great experience!  Hillary offered exceptional service!
A first-class Italian restaurant everything's homemade all the pasta is homemade
The atmosphere is incredible!!!
Nothing beats going to an Italian restaurant in the city and walking in to see the patron at the end of the bar watching everyone as rhey walk in. That's Italian!
Food was good.  Atmosphere was good.  I'd eat there again.

One of the best meals I've had in months. I ordered the tortellini, which was good but my family ordered the seafood ravioli and the baked penne and those dishes were amazing. Their house bottle of wine was also very affordable and delicious.
BEST toasted raviolis anywhere!!! Gitto's is my go to restaurant whenever I'm  in the city.
Pricey, service was not great, and food was just ok
Meatball sub on cheesy garlic bread with green peppers... followed up with some gooey butter cake... unbelievably delicious
Bad food, dirty, bad service, loud, expensive
Never disappoints!!!! Had the gnocchi and veal parm. Both were fantastic!

This is one of the best Italian restaurants in the St. Louis area. I have been coming here for over 15 years and will continue as long as they are open. The Chicken Parmesan is the best imho and the cheese garlic bread is delicious as well. The atomosphere is great, not formal but not casual either. The pictures on the wall are great and the owner is almost always at the bar in front to greet you as well. They have a full bar and a good assortment of wine as well. Should stop here and eat if and when you come to St Louis!!!
Alway a treat to eat there, great salad and any style pasta!
Good food and helpful, courteous staff. Love the atmosphere of by gone days.
OMG...some of the best food I've put in mouth. Get the cannaloni
incredibly  good  food
Food very tasty and prices reasonable
Lasagna lunch special was good, but it didn't come smothered in cheese like i had remembered in the past.
The best Italian I've ever had!
Visiting St. Louis. Had to try the toasted ravioli.
Stopped in for lunch and had a great salad and bread
Great food, good size portions. Very friendly! Plus, it feels like an authentic old Italian restaurant!
Great food and atmosphere!  Loved the French Dip!
Excellent
Great food and great service. Really cool atmosphere too.
Loved it!  A bit of a wait but we'll worth every minute.  Check it out if you like Italian.
Downtown institution features great food service and decor. Two Thumbs Up!!

Meh... Based on how busy this place was and how many good reviews I expected great food. It just wasn’t anything special. The pasta dishes had no flavor, bread was super basic and bland. My son ordered a strip steak that was just okay.  There were 3 of us dining... total was  $107 after 20% tip (service was good).  Disappointing food experience for the price.

The staff were friendly, and the atmosphere was typical of an old, nostalgic bar. It was clean and inviting. The food, however, was a disappointment. Had the spaghetti and meatballs, same as my manager. Mine had almost no sauce, while his was drowning in it. All of it was quite bland.
Perfect little hole in the wall. Was told by a friend that it was a must do. Food was amazing. Lasagna was perfect.
Food was great
Won't be going there again.   Service was slow.  Food was not worth the wait or the price.   My food was cold when I got it.
Excellent baked lasagna
Love this place.  Fantastic food, great staff, good wine list.  Would recommend it to anyone.
A little taste of Italy stateside!
Epic authentic Italian food!
Had the chicken nunzio. Very enjoyable and filling!

I went here for my birthday dinner and it was absolutely delicious I had to toasted ravioli which were small but that sauce was amazing. Then I had the lasagna which was absolutely delicious and so very cheesy which thank God it was. I also got the chocolate cake which was served ice-cold the server even was nice enough to write on my plate which was cold as well happy birthday which was so sweet. But an ice cold cake with frosting is not very good thankfully I took the cake home let it get to room temperature and it was so delish
Great Italian food and great atmosphere
Good food, terrible chees.  You have to explain "No provel cheese" over and over again and be very clear that it applies to all food brought to the table.
Great food, great service, great people.
First time going and it was awesome. Terrific service
Pleasant staff, great salad, really tasty food 2 nights in a row. Highly recommend.
Loved this place! Just had the Seafood Ravioli and it was an out of this world experience!

Ehhhh....It was okay. This was suggested by our hotel. It's walking distance from the Hyatt, and the walk over is cool because you have great views of the Arch and the Capitol. No booths here. Tables are smaller. Not much elbow room. I'm a booth gal, and also a Mountain Dew girl. They serve Coca-Cola. The service was okay. They didn't go out of their way to make sure we're having a great experience. I'm also a fettuccine girl, and NO. It was not fettuccine noodles. They were slightly undercooked, dry, and I know this is subjective, but the sauce had no taste at all. There are many other options in the STL.

Favorite food from my whole trip! The salad here is magical. I don't know what they put in it but, it's unreal! Also, had the Sugar Daddy cocktail which was out of this world. I'll definitely be back...again and again!

In town for a tournament at the Convention Complex and we were lucky enough to find and walk to Charlie Gitto's!  They were more than gracious in accommodating a large group of about 25, especially we kept calling to add more to our reservation.  Service and food were fantastic.  Especially liked the chicken parmesan and pasta with red sauce.  If you are in the neighborhood, I highly recommend you stop in.
Hadn't been there in about 12 years. Food and service was great as always. Thanks.
Not bad
The house salad is normally fantastic but last time there was barely any dressing and NO artichokes. They did not even discount the bill.

First time there during a family visit. Got the baked lasagna, the house special.  Amazing! Great bottle of pinot noir and dessert.  Service was super friendly. All-around great experience. Highly recommended.

Always a treat! Lots of family history & this was our last visit before my kids move out of state. Family all enjoyed their meals, the manicotti is a favorite, but mine was not as described on the menu (calamari fritti tossed in pepper relish)so substitutions were decided on in the kitchen adding red sauce of some kind that I can't eat as they haven't had the relish for months. By the time they took it back, removed the cup of red sauce & wiped off the dish where it had dripped & returned it to me, it had totally cooled. It's an appetizer but I used it for my lunch with a salad. The salad was good. I'll be back to St Louis periodically but will be eating on the hill, Cunetto's in the future.
Great service. Good food.
Service was very "teenager trying to get us out of the restaurant". They were out of everything and it just didn't taste as good as I had hoped to get to share with my out of town coworkers.
Fabulous food was perfect.

Lackluster...  Brought my wife and daughter to this establishment after recommended as a low-key and closer alternative to The Hill counterpart by a local at our hotel.  My daughter's basic Ravioli's meat filling had a very wonky taste.  We all tried it and told her to stop eating it.  Wife's Rigatoni Carbonara had absolutely NO taste.   We tried adding heaps of parmesan and oil.  Nothing could save this dish.  My own Chicken Parmesan was decent but nothing to write home about...  Gave my wife half so she would have something to eat.  She had given up on her dish after a few bites and our attempts to get flavor failed.  Waitress came to our table asking if we wanted to box up my wife and teenager's almost untouched plates.   I said 'no, the meals weren't their cup-of-tea'.  No asking what was wrong or offer of comp for the meals.  To top it all off, they started cleaning the place and stacking chairs in our area while we were still eating!  Only 10 mins after kirchen closed...  Just overall a bad experience.   With high prices to boot.  Don't think there's even anything they could offer to get me back there.
Went as part of a group of 15. Did a pretty good job serving.  Pasta was great, steak so so.
Fun place with great atmosphere with heavy woodwork and many signed pictures of celebrities.  Very good food and service, I had the veal which was great.

01/25/2019-Master Chef Ramsey needs to pay them a visit to Bring this Place Back to Life. I've been here 5 times and this time is my last coming here. I swear their food is old, stale. Something simple like a spaghetti MeatBall would be simple to make but instead each time is stale. Yuk!!  Overrated Restaurant.

Definitely authentic Italian in atmosphere and cuisine. Wait staff was polite and prompt. Food came out quickly. I ordered a vegetable dish which unfortunately was overcooked. Also, since I am a vegetarian I asked if the vegetable dish was vegetarian. I was told it was but last time I checked prosciutto isn't vegetarian. I removed from the dish throughly and moved on.
Great Italian food, service excellent during their busiest hours
recommend eating here while you walk around and view the arch at night
Just a nice quaint restaurant.  Good quality food.  Pleasant staff.  Parking is offered next to the building for a small fee but really worth it due to the restaurants location.

Wonderful service. Our waitress was terrific. We had a group of 14, with 5 children under 6 in our group. Our waitress kept checking on us from the start, all the way through the meal/dessert; with a happy smile and she was very attentive! We will definitely be returning!
Good place
Horrible.  Avoid at all costs.
Best in STL
Goto the location on the hill.
Toasted raviolis were delicious the lasagna was even better.
Best tortellini in town
Decent Italian food
Ate at the bar. They ate me also. By far the best St. Louis has to offer for as thin as that building is. Super charming low key 5 stars.

Don't understand how this place has 4 stars.  Steer clear of this one.  I'm guessing it used to be pretty good but the experience we had begs to differ.  My steak was garbage.  The dessert was ok.  The service blows.

Excellent, as always. The luncheon special, Chicken Parmesan in a bed of spaghetti with marinara sauce, and an Italian-dressing side salad. Coffee was great too. A new twist, olive oil to go with the Italian bread.
Excellent lasagna but the spaghetti and meatballs is my favorite. Very old school Italian joint. Very high class with excellent service.
Came in for a quick drink after work and had a great time. Great atmosphere and affordable fair. Take a jot inside if you get the chance!

6-Nov-2018.  I was surprised that I was disappointed tonight!  I had high expectations... And they were not met.  I started with soup as the appetizer. Ham and bean. The soup was VERY oversalted. I like well seasoned soup but this was too salty to enjoy. Also, I ordered the chicken parm as my main dinner entree.  Chicken parm is always best when served in thin cutlets. Charlie Gitto's prepares a huge chunk 'o chicken breast, too thick to qualify as a typical chicken cutlet. It's simply understood that the best chicken parm involves thin filet cutlets of the breast, gently fried and covered in marinara sauce and MOZZARELLA. I must have missed the part on the menu stating that some other cheese would be used... Was it provel cheese? It was slimy rather than dense and stretchy. But above all, what really bothered me was that the pasta served under the chicken was cool and not hot.  I love Italian food... I seek it whenever I travel to STL for business. Unfortunately, this meal was not enjoyable. No need to come back here with so many better options available.

Old school STL location with walls filled with memorabilia capturing the prime of STL. The food is traditional STL italian with great portions and flavor.  Only downside is the only cheese available is provel. But I'm not from st Louis so I'm a hater.  Definitely check this place out if your down town.
Best Italian in St. Louis
Good sandwich for lunch

I love this place! My friends and I go to St Louis every year for a convention and were recommended this place by our hotel several years ago.  We make it a must do stop every year now.  Great ambiance.  Excellent food and service.  Not for the fast food budget though but it won't break the bank.

Fast. Friendly. Tasty. We were in town for a convention and we’re running out of time to grab dinner before the evening session started. We popped in here and it was incredible. We explained we were in a bit of a rush and the staff were so accommodating.  The carbonara was really tasty but the cheesy bread was AMAZING.
It was great. I had the chicken parmigiana, and it was perhaps the best I've ever had!
Great Italiano Meatball subs
Great food, historic, cozy
Great food, service and wine
Great Authentic Italian. Outstanding Mussels Marinara.
Great place

This place is consistently good. I always enjoy visiting with friends. I do recommend calling ahead, even for small groups. You can't go wrong with any of the house specials and the prices are very reasonable.
The marinara sauce tasted like tomato paste with a bit of oregano.
Fine Italian Dining experience...friendly staff , clean rest. And food was excellent!

The positives are location, friendly staff, and I loved the atmosphere. The food was horrible! It didn't taste freshly prepared at all, disappointing for the prices being charged. No merlot, no cannolis, out cheesecake, bartender didn't know how to make simple drink choices. I think this place has the potential of being fabulous. Thank God for your serving staff.
Great service, okay food, lasagne was very good, ravioli was cold. I would go early as we were told they were out of bread for the evening-an Italian restaurant ran out bread.

Travelled over 3000 miles from Scotland to have the worst Italian meal ever. Don't know if this is a tourist trap, but is certainly recommended by the local hotels.  You can get better from the worst of restaurants in glasgow.  Bye a jar and some  dried pasta, far superior to anything you will get here. Truly truly abysmal.

The service and ambience is great however the food is truly abysmal.  I have only once before had a worse italian and that was on the canary islands.  Do yourself a favour and go somewhere else. The food here is terrible.
Really great atmosphere. Food was bad from top to bottom with the exception of the toasted ravioli.

Well... very disappointed. the food looks good and even if it taste “good” it wasn’t what we ordered. The Carbonara pasta that was serve to us was made with heavy cream which it should NOT have any cream added, the salad was 3 peace’s of tomato cut down the middle and tons of onions and cheese on top, this salad do not have any onions but in here the chef thinks it does. place is nice and the waitress was awesome, thanks to her i leave 2 starts and not just 1.

Overall experience very poor. I was a long time server so I typically give restaurants the benefit of the doubt but this place was underwhelming from top to bottom. The salad was obviously hours old and slimy and you could almost see thru it. The bread wasn’t complementary and we asked for some hoping to improve on the salad, but it had no taste at all. Literally like eating copy paper. The kids wouldn’t eat the cheese pizza.... and cheese pizza is hard to mess up. My entree was super salty and I’m a person who always salts my food. So 2 adults and 2 kids $90 and other than my Budweiser draft beers nothing was good. Being from out of town and visiting St. Louis for fall break we were really looking forward to a nice dinner after a long drive. Very disappointed!
It was ok
Awesome food
Bustling and cozy. Fast service and decent food. Come early to beat the crowds on game day. Toasted ravioli, pasta bolognese with meatballs, and the lasagna are tasty and served in hearty portions.

I love the physical space, the tiled floors, the wood walls, the pictures of various sports stars on the walls.   It almost reminds me of someplace in New Orleans.   Add to that the rest of the decor and the music playing in the background and you feel like you've stepped back into the 1940's. It's a great place to have downtown as it's a nice balance of casual and elegant.  We've been going there for years, and have had some up and down experiences.   One time we got their deep fried cheese and it was cold.  We sent it back and when it came out again it was still cold.   Other times we've had nice meals with no problems.  The food itself is decent but the prices have steadily gone up over the years which makes me expect a bit more but really nothing has changed that I have seen.   This probably makes us go less than we normally would.  Still there's something that I like about this place and want to see it stick around.  Check out it if you want a unique slice of St. Louis history.
